 |CKBDarkwind Reputation
|WKO~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 |YKOYour reputation is shaped by what you do in the world.
At higher levels it affects whether you are known as a Hero,
an Adventurer, or a Villain.

Guild membership alone does not decide your reputation. A paladin
can fall, a thief can do useful work, and a mage can be feared or
admired depending on what their magic does. Reputation changes come
from actions: quests, divine offerings, public praise or slander,
resurrection, theft, desecration, and other notable deeds.

Some deeds also leave hidden marks that help the world understand
why you are known the way you are. Mercy, terror, honor, faith,
nature, crime, secrecy, blood, service, and public notoriety may all
matter to future reactions.

When a deed affects your reputation, you may feel a small sign of it.
Those signs are intentionally broad. DarkWind will not show the exact
weights, thresholds, or every hidden mark, but it will increasingly let
you know when your actions have begun to matter.

Use |YKBreputation|YKO to reflect on your public renown, common whispers,
and recent signs. This command describes the shape of your reputation
without turning it into a ledger.

Deeds with clear divine meaning can also tug the omen cycle. Merciful and
service-minded acts may carry toward Mitra, nature and restoration toward
Gaea, and fear or shadowed ambition toward Set. During a god's Holy Hour,
matching deeds carry farther.

Current public reputation labels:
  |GKBHero|YKO       A positive heroism reputation.
  |WKBAdventurer|YKO A neutral heroism reputation.
  |RKBVillain|YKO    A negative heroism reputation.

As the system grows, reputation may influence rumors, NPC reactions,
guild rites, shops, services, bounty pressure, safehouses, quest
branches, and other world responses.

